---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { DISCORD_URL, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../site';
---

<Base
  path="/terms"
  title="Terms of Service — Voxhelm"
  description="The terms for using Voxhelm, the Windows voice assistant: subscriptions, acceptable use, and disclaimers."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
    <a href="/" class="text-[13px] font-light uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 transition-colors hover:text-white">← Back</a>
    <h1 class="font-garamond mt-8 text-4xl font-normal text-white sm:text-5xl">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-[13px] font-light italic text-white/40">Last updated: July 2026.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[15px] font-light leading-relaxed text-white/70">
      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">The service</h2>
        <p>Voxhelm is a Windows voice assistant that operates your computer on your instructions. You're responsible for the actions you ask it to take. Voxhelm asks for confirmation before destructive actions, but you remain in control of your machine and accounts. The assistant is designed to decline requests that violate the acceptable-use policy below.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Subscriptions &amp; billing</h2>
        <p>Hosted AI requires a paid subscription billed through Stripe. Plans renew automatically until cancelled. You can cancel anytime; access continues to the end of the paid period. Fair-use limits apply per plan.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Right of withdrawal (EU/EEA customers)</h2>
        <p>
          If you are a consumer in the EU/EEA, you have the right to withdraw from your
          subscription within 14 days of purchase without giving a reason. By completing
          checkout and requesting that your subscription start immediately, you expressly
          ask us to begin providing the service before the withdrawal period ends, and you
          acknowledge that if you withdraw after service has started, you owe a
          proportionate amount for the service already provided up to that point, rather
          than a full refund. To withdraw, email
          <a class="text-white underline underline-offset-4" href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>
          with an unambiguous statement (a simple "I withdraw from my subscription" is enough).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>Voxhelm may be used only for lawful purposes. You must not use it to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
          <li>commit or facilitate any crime or fraud;</li>
          <li>access accounts, devices, or networks you don't own or aren't authorised to use;</li>
          <li>create or distribute malware, or attack others' systems;</li>
          <li>harass, threaten, stalk, impersonate, or covertly monitor another person;</li>
          <li>access, create, or distribute sexually explicit content or any content that is illegal in your jurisdiction;</li>
          <li>infringe others' intellectual-property or privacy rights;</li>
          <li>circumvent the usage limits, safety measures, or security of the service.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">The assistant is designed to decline such requests. We may suspend or terminate accounts used in violation of this policy — without refund for the remaining subscription period where the violation is serious or repeated.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Your responsibility &amp; indemnity</h2>
        <p>Voxhelm executes your instructions on your computer, under your control and signed in to your accounts. You are solely responsible for the instructions you give and for the actions taken on your behalf. If your use of Voxhelm in violation of these terms or of applicable law leads to third-party claims, damages, or costs (including reasonable legal fees) against us, you agree to indemnify and hold us harmless from them.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>Voxhelm is provided "as is". Automated actions can make mistakes; review important actions. To the extent permitted by law, we're not liable for indirect or consequential damages arising from use of the software.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-white">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions: email
          <a class="text-white underline underline-offset-4" href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>
          or reach us in the
          <a class="text-white underline underline-offset-4" href={DISCORD_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Voxhelm Discord</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
